headline_main: Transgender Lives: Your Stories: Shane Alejandro Ortega

abstract: I came to the conclusion that I had prayed for the wrong thing—I prayed that God would fix me. I discovered that God didn't need to fix me.

abstract: At the age of 65, I knew I couldn’t keep up the pretense much longer.  I would go crazy or be dead.

headline_main: Transgender Lives: Your Stories: Katherine Birdsall

abstract: My mother and family were extremely supportive and loving.  My children have all but written me off, and I’m hoping with time, things will progress.
